cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC

This paper involves the development of a method for automatic monitoring of nursing notes for signs and symptoms of infection, which requires natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which covers topics related to the interaction between computers and society, including natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also involves the use of electronic medical records, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The development of the machine learning model involves classification, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of machine learning for healthcare applications falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the development of a tool for healthcare professionals, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
